Lecture 13

Social Network Analysis

Nodes and Edges

SNAnodesedges(graph)

The entities are referred to as nodes (or vertices, actors) () of a graph, while the connections are edges (or links, ties, relations) ().

If the distinction between source and target is meaningful, the network is directed. If the distinction is not meaningful, the network is undirected.
